{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01EDt86FKWLux8bd9oz2QfQY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the problem clearly. The `elasticsearch.yml` configmap is missing the `cluster.initial_master_nodes` setting, which is required for a fresh Elasticsearch cluster to form. This is a bootstrap-only setting that tells the cluster which nodes can form the initial master election quorum.\n\nThe configmap has:\n- `cluster.name: es-cluster`\n- `node.name: ${POD_NAME}`\n- `node.roles: [ master, data, ingest ]`\n- `network.host: 0.0.0.0`\n- `discovery.seed_hosts` pointing to the three nodes\n- `node.store.allow_mmap: false`\n\nBut it's missing `cluster.initial_master_nodes`, which is essential for bootstrap in Elasticsearch 7+. I need to add this setting to the configmap, then do a rolling restart so the pods pick up the new configuration. Once the cluster forms successfully, I should remove the bootstrap setting and restart again since it's only meant for initial cluster formation. The key distinction is whether the data directory uses persistent storage or ephemeral storage. With a PVC, I can safely remove `cluster.initial_master_nodes` after bootstrap and restart—the cluster stays up because each node retains its state on disk. But with emptyDir, removing the setting would break cluster reformation on restart. Let me look at the StatefulSet configuration to see what storage approach is being used.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4993,"cache_read_input_tokens":34995,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4993},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5456b79a-91c2-4890-992d-eb00820b8b7c","uuid":"15147caa-ea59-4574-8f9e-25f7c3d26677",