{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019UKP8RxuowBioonVLkyf6c","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, the PVCs are Bound. So the cluster has persistent storage. The issue is that `cluster.initial_master_nodes` is missing from the configmap.\n\nHere's my plan:\n\n1. **Add `cluster.initial_master_nodes` to the configmap** - list all 3 node names\n2. **Rolling restart the StatefulSet** - pods need to be restarted to pick up the new config (since the configmap is mounted as a file, but ES reads it at startup)\n3. **Wait for the cluster to form and be healthy**\n4. **Remove `cluster.initial_master_nodes` from the configmap** - this is only needed for bootstrap\n5. **Rolling restart again** - the nodes have persistent state on disk now, so they'll re-form the cluster without needing that setting\n\nThe key insight is that since the configmap is mounted directly into the container and Elasticsearch reads it at startup, I need to restart the pods to apply changes. Once the cluster forms and saves its state to the PVCs, I can safely remove the bootstrap setting and restart one more time.\n\nFor the restart strategy, all three nodes need to restart together initially since none have cluster state yet, but I should use `kubectl rollout restart` to handle this cleanly. After the cluster is established, subsequent restarts can be rolling (one pod at a time) since each node will have its state persisted on disk.\n\nActually, I'm realizing there's a timing issue with rolling restarts—if I restart pods one at a time, the first pod to come back up won't have enough peers to form a quorum with just the `initial_master_nodes` setting, since the other two are still running the old configuration without that setting. The restarting pod will try to discover the others via `discovery.seed_hosts`, but they won't be eligible master nodes yet.\n\nThe solution is to update the configmap first to add `cluster.initial_master_nodes` with all three nodes, then delete all the pods simultaneously so they restart together and can elect a master with a proper quorum. Since the config is mounted with `subPath`, the file won't update automatically—the pods need to be restarted to pick up the changes.\n\nOnce the cluster forms and reaches a healthy state, I'll remove the bootstrap setting from the configmap and do a proper rolling restart one pod at a time, checking cluster health between each restart.\n\nFor the initial restart in step 2, since the cluster is completely down with no master elected, I can safely delete all three pods at once so they restart together with the new config and form the cluster. Then for the rolling restart to remove the bootstrap setting, I'll use `kubectl rollout restart` on the StatefulSet, which should restart pods in reverse order (2, 1, 0) and wait for each to become ready before moving to the next. The readiness probe checks if port 9200 is accepting connections, which should happen once Elasticsearch is up and rejoined to the cluster. The solution is to delete all three pods simultaneously so they restart together and can form the cluster. I'm running a kubectl command to remove the pods, which will trigger the StatefulSet controller to recreate them all at once with the new configuration.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":509,"cache_read_input_tokens":42121,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":509},"output_tokens":29,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5456b79a-91c2-4890-992d-eb00820b8b7c","uuid":"b832da44-a5c0-4993-8c53-9826102a1607","request_id":"req_011CcLtvBsYsD3x6i1ZSF8wL"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019UKP8RxuowBioonVLkyf6c","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The problem is clear: the configmap has `discovery.seed_hosts` but is missing `cluster.initial_master_nodes`, which ES 7+ requires to bootstrap the initial master election. The PVCs are bound with persistent storage.\n\n**Plan:**\n1. Add `cluster.initial_master_nodes` to the configmap\n2. Delete all 3 pods simultaneously (can't do rolling restart when no cluster exists — need all 3 to start together for quorum)\n3. Wait for cluster to form and be healthy\n4. Remove `cluster.initial_master_nodes` from the configmap (bootstrap-only)\n5. Rolling restart one pod at a time — nodes will rejoin using their persisted cluster state"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":509,"cache_read_input_tokens":42121,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":509},"output_tokens":29,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5456b79a-91c2-4890-992d-eb00820b8b7c","uuid":"02dc29ce-cff5-4721-a1f1-c9a9e815e1d4","request_id":"req_011CcLtvBsYsD3x6i1ZSF8wL"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019UKP8RxuowBioonVLkyf6c","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Drke21nyDNuJ6U5RTcijnk","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"export KUBECONFIG=/mydata/karma/runs/long-rererun/elasticsearch-long-all-cases-marathon-20260623_212244/bundle/kubeconfig && kubectl -n elasticsearch patch configmap es-config --type=merge -p '{\"data\":{\"elasticsearch.yml\":\"cluster.name: es-cluster\\nnode.name: ${POD_NAME}\\nnode.roles: [ master, data, ingest ]\\nnetwork.host: 0.0.0.0\\ndiscovery.seed_hosts:\\n  - es-cluster-0.es-cluster\\n  - es-cluster-1.es-cluster\\n  - es-cluster-2.es-cluster\\ncluster.initial_master_nodes:\\n  - es-cluster-0\\n  - es-cluster-1\\n  - es-cluster-2\\nnode.store.allow_mmap: false\\n\"}}'","description":"Add cluster.initial_master_nodes to ES configmap"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":509,"cache_read_input_tokens":42121,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":509},"output_tokens":29,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5456b79a-91c2-4890-992d-eb00820b8b7c","uuid":"3ec453bd-cb68-46a6-b18c-932c66815901","request_id":"req_011CcLtvBsYsD3x6i1ZSF8wL"}
