{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Y1mfuApqytCgBZY2yUMmz2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All goals are met:\n\n**Root cause:** The `es-config` ConfigMap was missing `cluster.initial_master_nodes`, which ES 7+ requires to bootstrap the initial master election. Without it, all nodes log \"master not discovered yet\" indefinitely.\n\n**What was done:**\n\n1. **Added `cluster.initial_master_nodes`** listing all 3 nodes to the ConfigMap.\n\n2. **Restarted all 3 pods simultaneously** — required because the cluster had no state yet and needed all 3 to start together to reach quorum (2/3). The `subPath` mount means pods don't pick up ConfigMap changes without a restart.\n\n3. **Cluster formed** — status green, `es-cluster-2` elected as master, all 3 nodes joined.\n\n4. **Removed `cluster.initial_master_nodes`** from the ConfigMap — it's a bootstrap-only setting; leaving it in is dangerous because it can interfere with re-bootstrap scenarios.\n\n5. **Rolling restart** (pod-2 → pod-1 → pod-0, one at a time) — each pod restarted with the clean config, rejoined using its persisted PVC cluster state, and cluster stayed **green** with 3 nodes throughout. A future rolling restart is safe to perform the same way."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":701,"cache_read_input_tokens":48931,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":701},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5456b79a-91c2-4890-992d-eb00820b8b7c","uuid":"9f98b48f-904a-4cff-b9eb-2261a013b6ab","request_id":"req_011CcLuYst7269J8ZrCYFy1N"}
